DATA CLOUD
Data Stream Settings

You can edit the settings of data streams that use Amazon S3, Google Cloud Storage (GCS), and SFTP connectors.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Edition
REFRESH MODE	DESCRIPTION
Upsert	When your data stream is created in upsert mode, for each refresh, if there's new data it’s added and if there's an update to existing data it's updated.
Full Refresh	When your data stream is created in full refresh mode, during each refresh cycle all existing data is deleted and replaced with the newly imported dataset.
DATA STREAM SETTING	DESCRIPTION
Refresh only new files	

When set, all files are retrieved when the data stream is first run. For subsequent runs only new files are retrieved.

IMPORTANT This setting is deprecated for S3 data streams. An S3 data stream always retrieves only new files. If you want to retrieve all files satisfying the data stream file name specification, click Refresh Now on the record home page and select Refresh All Files option. This selection applies only for the current refresh. For subsequent runs only new files are retrieved.

Log an error if no file is found	

When enabled and no file is found during the data stream run, the line item in the refresh history for that run shows a “failure”. A notification is triggered if you subscribe to data stream failure notifications.

When this setting isn’t enabled and no file is found during the data stream run, the refresh history shows zero records but with a "success" status.


Is headerless file retrieval enabled	

When set, Data Cloud accepts the data records without headers.

IMPORTANT Make sure the order of fields is maintained in the incoming data records to avoid data corruption.

Schedule	Set the frequency of the file refresh.
Refresh initial file immediately	

When set Data Cloud doesn't wait until the scheduled run and retrieves the initial file immediately.

You can now run an immediate file refresh for only new files or all the files that are in your storage.
